Rituals: 3
Evasion: 2
Attack: ‚ÄúHylden Surge‚Äù ‚Äì Deals 5 static damage and forces a DR 2 Spirit save. Failure: the victim takes 1 corruption.
Ability: ‚ÄúSoul Override‚Äù ‚Äì Once per encounter, hijack the body of a dying creature (under 5 HP) and resume combat at half HP.
Aura: ‚ÄúReality Rift‚Äù ‚Äì Enemies in a 2-tile radius suffer -1 to DR saves vs. spells and psychic effects.

üî• Variants
Hylden Warlord ‚Äì Possessed human champions twisted into elite combatants; wield corrupted weapons and channel forbidden rites.
Hylden Whisperer ‚Äì Psychic controller and possession specialist.
Hylden Forgebeast ‚Äì Biomechanical monstrosity used in siege warfare.

üß† Tactics
Hylden are not berserkers. They coordinate, manipulate, and corrupt from behind constructs and thralls. When threatened, they teleport, retreat, or possess.

üéÅ Loot (Optional)
Hylden Technology Shard (infuses one spell with +1 DR difficulty)
Possessed Bone (used in rituals to pierce veil between realms)
Hylden Bioplate (Light armor, Reduces Damage by 2, immune to Spectral damage)
GM Note: Use sparingly; Hylden are world-shaping foes meant to test moral boundaries, spiritual defenses, and the cost of resisting fate.

